Refined Prompt

Here's the updated prompt with the Target Audience section added, and Requirements slightly adjusted to reflect a more luxury-focused sensibility:

Role:
You are a senior website designer with expertise in e-commerce and fashion retail platforms, skilled in translating brand identity into functional, scalable digital experiences.
Objective:
Design and generate a complete, production-ready website for a fashion brand — covering visual design, page structure, core functionality, and technical architecture.
Background:
The brand produces contemporary, designer, and customised clothing for all age groups (kids, teens, adults, seniors). It needs an online presence that balances boutique sophistication with everyday accessibility, supporting three core customer journeys: browsing the catalogue, completing purchases, and booking personalised styling consultations. The brand is positioning itself as approachable luxury — refined, but not intimidating.
Target Audience:
Luxury-class consumers who expect a premium, exclusive shopping experience — customers who value craftsmanship, personalised service, and refined aesthetics over budget-driven or mass-market shopping cues. The website should feel like a private boutique experience translated online, not a generic retail store.
Requirements:
Design & Navigation

Modern, clean design pattern with a minimal, intuitive top navigation bar (Home, Shop, Customisation, Consultation, About, Contact, Account)
Sticky header with search bar and cart icon always visible
Consistent visual rhythm using generous white space, refined grid-based layouts, and an overall unhurried, premium browsing pace

Inventory & Shop

Dedicated Shop/Inventory page listing all existing products in a responsive grid, presented with an editorial, lookbook-style feel rather than a dense retail grid
Filters for category (Men/Women/Kids), age group, size, color, and price range
Sorting options (newest, price low-high, popularity)
Product cards showing image, name, price, and quick "add to cart" on hover, with elegant, understated hover reveals

Purchase Flow

Individual product detail pages with multiple high-quality images, size/color selectors, stock availability, and rich description (materials, craftsmanship details)
Shopping cart with quantity adjustment and price summary
Secure, seamless checkout flow integrated with Razorpay for payment processing
Order confirmation and email/SMS notification triggers, written in a refined, personal tone

Consultation Feature

Dedicated Consultation page allowing customers to book a personal styling/design session, positioned as a white-glove, concierge-style service
Simple form (name, contact, preferred date/time, style preferences) or an embedded calendar-based scheduling widget
Confirmation message/email after booking, reflecting a personalised, attentive tone

Customisation Feature

Dedicated Customisation page where users can configure made-to-order garments (fabric, fit, measurements, style preferences) via a step-by-step form or configurator, emphasizing exclusivity and craftsmanship

Interactivity & UX

Smooth, subtle hover effects, fade-in transitions, and refined micro-interactions on buttons, product cards, and menus — nothing flashy or attention-grabbing
Mobile-friendly touch interactions (swipeable image galleries, collapsible filters)
Clear, minimal-step checkout (ideally 3 steps or fewer: cart → details → payment), designed to feel effortless and unhurried

Full Page List
Homepage, Shop/Inventory, Product Detail, Customisation, Consultation, Cart/Checkout, About, Contact, User Account/Order History
Color & Visual Style

Strictly soft pastel palette: blush pink, powder blue, sage green, soft lilac, cream — used as base tones with one muted accent color for CTAs (buttons, highlights)
Refined typography: a soft serif or minimal sans-serif for headings, clean sans-serif for body text — conveying elegance and exclusivity
High-quality, editorial-style product photography as the primary visual focus; minimal decorative elements, ample negative space to reinforce a premium feel

Constraints:

Color usage must remain strictly within the subtle pastel range specified — no bold, dark, neon, or highly saturated colors anywhere in the UI, including buttons, banners, and icons
All payment processing must be handled exclusively through Razorpay — no other payment gateway should be referenced or integrated
No stock template layouts — every section must be uniquely structured for this brand, avoiding generic mass-market e-commerce patterns

Output Format:
Generate a complete, structured website specification/prompt — including page-by-page layout description, component list (header, filters, product cards, forms, checkout flow), color and typography guidelines, and technical/backend requirements — formatted so it can be directly fed into an AI website-generation tool (e.g., Framer AI, 10Web, or similar) to produce a functional, ready-to-launch site.
Evaluation Criteria:

The generated website must be fully responsive, rendering correctly and adjusting layout seamlessly across mobile phones, tablets, laptops, and desktop screens
The design must be entirely original — no duplication or close resemblance to the layout, visual identity, or structural pattern of any existing fashion e-commerce website
The site's architecture must be scalable and optimized to handle heavy concurrent user traffic without slowdowns (efficient image loading, caching strategy, CDN-readiness, backend scalability)
Razorpay integration must function correctly within the checkout flow, and the pastel color constraint must be visibly and consistently applied across all pages
The overall experience must feel aligned with luxury-class expectations — premium, exclusive, and personalised rather than mass-market

