Refined Prompt

Role:
You are a senior AI expert and mentor, skilled at simplifying complex technical concepts for beginners.
Objective:
Write a detailed, easy-to-follow tutorial/write-up introducing Artificial Intelligence to complete beginners.
Background:
This tutorial is meant for readers who have no prior technical background in AI and are encountering these concepts for the first time. It should build understanding from the ground up, using plain language and relatable comparisons rather than jargon.
Target Audience:
College students with little to no prior exposure to AI, machine learning, or related technical fields.
Requirements:

Introduction: A simple, engaging opening explaining what AI is and why it matters today
Core Concepts of AI: Explain foundational ideas (e.g., AI, Machine Learning, Deep Learning) in simple terms, showing how they relate to one another
Applications of AI: Cover key areas where AI is used (e.g., healthcare, education, entertainment, transportation, business)
Real-Life Examples: Include everyday, relatable examples students would recognize (e.g., Netflix recommendations, Google Maps, voice assistants, ChatGPT)
Diagrams: Include suitable diagrams or visual descriptions to explain core concepts (e.g., a diagram showing AI → ML → Deep Learning as nested circles, or a simple flow diagram of how AI makes a decision)
Word limit: Strictly 1000 words total
Structure the write-up with clear headings for each section so it's easy to navigate

Constraints:

Do not use any aggressive, abusive, or offensive language
Content must remain appropriate and relevant specifically for a student audience — no unrelated technical tangents or overly advanced jargon

Output Format:
A well-structured, standalone tutorial/article (within 1000 words) with clear section headings, simple explanations, real-life examples, and at least one described/illustrated diagram — ready to be published or shared as a beginner-friendly AI learning resource.
Evaluation Criteria:

Language must be simple and easy to understand, accessible even to a complete beginner with no technical background
Concepts must build logically from basic to slightly more advanced, without losing clarity at any point
Diagrams/visuals must genuinely aid understanding, not just decorate the text

