Refined Prompt:

Role:
You are a senior marketing manager and campaign planning expert with experience in luxury fashion brand positioning and multi-channel campaign execution.
Objective:
Create a detailed marketing campaign plan for launching a new, unique style of garments by a luxury fashion brand.
Background:
The brand is currently struggling to position itself effectively in the market and is launching a new distinctive garment line as a strategic move to re-establish its identity and stand out from competitors. The campaign needs to be impactful enough to meaningfully shift brand perception and drive real customer acquisition.
Target Audience:
Medium-income group females, aged 25 to 50, primarily located in North India, including both urban centers and nearby sub-urban areas.
Requirements:

Include both a physical/offline campaign (e.g., in-store events, pop-ups, print/OOH advertising, mall activations) and a digital campaign (social media, influencer marketing, digital ads, email/SMS marketing)
Primary geographic focus: North India, with deliberate outreach extending into sub-urban areas near major urban centers (not just metro cities)
Include launch discounts or introductory offers wherever feasible to drive initial trial and conversions (e.g., early-bird pricing, first-purchase discounts, referral incentives)
Provide a clear campaign timeline/phasing (pre-launch, launch, post-launch sustenance)
Include a suggested budget allocation breakdown across physical and digital channels
Include suggested KPIs/success metrics to track campaign performance (footfall, engagement, conversions, sales, ROI)

Constraints:

The campaign must be strictly targeted at female customers aged 25 to 50 only
Total campaign expenditure must not exceed a budget of ₹50 Lakh
Village/rural areas must not be targeted — focus should remain on urban and sub-urban zones only

Output Format:
A detailed, structured marketing campaign plan document including: campaign objective summary, target audience profile, channel-wise strategy (physical + digital), geographic rollout plan, budget allocation breakdown, discount/offer strategy, timeline, and measurable success metrics/KPIs.
Evaluation Criteria:

The campaign must be realistically capable of generating profit and meaningful customer acquisition within the given budget
Budget allocation must be practical and proportionate to expected reach and impact across both physical and digital channels
The plan must clearly show how success/ROI will be measured post-campaign



